%I A397251 #7 Jun 24 2026 17:12:31
%S A397251 36,255,264,306,588,1074,1224,1360,1836,1920,2016,2112,2952,3520,3948,
%T A397251 4394,4605,4935,5000,9963,10080,11136,11736,16872,19200
%N A397251 Integers x such that there exist three integers 0<x<=y and 0<z<=t such that sigma(x)*psi(x)^2 = sigma(y)*psi(y)^2 = x^3 + y^3 + z^3 + t^3.
%C A397251 The numbers x, y, z and t form a sigma*psi^2-cubic quadruple.
%H A397251 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://hal.science/hal-05303937">On σψ-quadratic k-tuples and related generalizations</a>, hal-05303937, 2025.
%H A397251 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://github.com/Stoyan16/Sigma-psi-2-cubic-quadruples/blob/main/A397251">Python program</a> (GitHub)
%e A397251 (264, 376, 272, 528) is such a quadruple because sigma(264) * psi(264)^2 = sigma(376) * psi(376)^2 = 720 * 576^2 = 264^3 + 376^3 + 272^3 + 528^3.
%o A397251 (Python) # See Links.
%Y A397251 Cf. A000203, A001615, A003327, A385397, A391534, A396076, A396407, A396459.
